<paragraph id="8BDB9B17317CBD033BE0F9E89B9AAA14" blockId="5.[151,1436,1605,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
Considering that the distinctive general structure of the male antennae is diagnostic for the genus, we feel that the highly asymmetrical rami of the male antennomeres 
<quantity id="4C9C36F2317CBD03385FF9C09C63ABB4" box="[808,891,1645,1671]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.905" metricValueMax="2.794" metricValueMin="1.016" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" unit="in" value="7.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="4.0">4-11 in</quantity>
this taxon warrant species, rather than subspecies, distinction. This species appears to be restricted to the Colorado Desert of SW Arizona, SE California, extending into Baja California (Norte) and, possibly, Baja California Sur, 
<collectingCountry id="F373DB87317CBD033F67F9109B76ABE4" box="[1040,1134,1725,1751]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. Although the few specimens we have seen from the latter state come closest to 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317CBD03384CF9489CB0ABCD" box="[827,936,1765,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Knowltonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calida">
<emphasis id="B9104705317CBD03384CF9489CB0ABCD" box="[827,936,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. calida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the male antennae, nevertheless there are differences, and much more material for study is needed from the peninsula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37EC89C317CBD003BB2F8989A2EADE9" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDB9B17317CBD033BB2F8989E7FAADC" blockId="5.[151,1436,1605,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF5E6E6317CBD033BB2F8989E46AA7C" author="Knull" box="[197,350,1845,1871]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refString="Knull, J. N. (1958) A new subspecies of Chrysobothris biramosa (Fisher) (Coleoptera: Buprestidae). The Ohio Journal of Science, 58, 96." type="journal article" year="1958">
Knull (
<number id="3DAC8930317CBD033A6FF8989E4DAA7C" box="[280,341,1845,1871]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="1958.0">1958</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
distinguished this taxon from “typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317CBD03385FF8989CA1AA7D" box="[808,953,1845,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biramosa">
<emphasis id="B9104705317CBD03385FF8989CA1AA7D" box="[808,953,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">C. biramosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” only by its dorsal green color. He made no mention of any other difference, and it is strange he overlooked the antennal character. The color no longer works well as a diagnostic character, though 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317CBD0339D0F8289C0BAAAD" box="[679,787,1925,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Knowltonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calida">
<emphasis id="B9104705317CBD0339D0F8289C0BAAAD" box="[679,787,1925,1950]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. calida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is uniformly deep green, sometimes with a bluish cast, while green forms of 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317CBD033AE5F8009D3BAAF5" box="[402,547,1965,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biramosa">
<emphasis id="B9104705317CBD033AE5F8009D3BAAF5" box="[402,547,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. biramosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are lighter green, often with coppery reflections that are more notable at the base of the elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB9B17317FBD003BB2FF359A2EADE9" blockId="6.[151,1436,152,218]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
This species has been collected on 
<taxonomicName id="4C64E094317FBD00392BFF359C58AD82" box="[604,832,152,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lentiformis">
